Cubrim License Summary

Cubrim is free for non-commercial use under the Cubrim non-commercial license.
Commercial use requires a paid Arcanada commercial license.
Standard commercial target: USD 50/year per named user seat or per installed device.

License and release fetches send only a random install_id UUID, operating
system, CPU architecture, Cubrim CLI version, and event type. The server also
sees and logs the request IP address. These records are used only for license
management, release delivery, abuse prevention, and installation counting.
Cubrim never sends hostnames, OS usernames, file paths, compressed content, or
project data.

Temporary canonical license URL: https://cubrim.com/legal/cubrim-license
Future canonical license URL: https://legal.arcanada.ai/policies/cubrim/license/v1.0
